		"description": "<p>Your familiar has become so much more, able to transform into a vicious attack beast or a sturdy mount at your command, it is a steadfast companion and a provider of options for you. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.sa8lr3mktzty24m6]{Frog Fangs} invocation if you do not already have it and another invocation you qualify for if you do.</li>\n<li>Your familiar&rsquo;s AC cannot be lower than your warlock level + your wielder level.</li>\n<li>When your familiar hits with an attack, you can spend an artifact charge or warlock spell point to have it inject venom into the target. The target takes 1d4 points of necrotic damage and must save against your spell save DC or be poisoned until the end of its next turn.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Your familiar is an attack trained shape-shifter.\n<ul>\n<li>Your familiar can increase to Medium size as an action. While in this form, it gains temporary hit points equal to your warlock level + your wielder level + your proficiency bonus + your spellcasting modifier. The temporary hit points and size increase last until you begin a rest or dismiss it. In either case, the familiar returns to its usual size and the temporary hit points vanish.</li>\n<li>While it is Medium-sized, your familiar can increase to Large size as an action. While in this form, it is semi-spectral (gaining resistance to all damage except force and psychic), and retains the temporary hit points from its Medium sized form, but cannot attack. Its Speed increases to 10 + (10 x your proficiency bonus) and you can ride it as a mount. If it has a flying or swim speed, you can have one of those speeds increase instead. It can return to medium size as an action, losing the semi-spectral nature but regaining its attack or if you begin a rest while it is Large, it reverts to its usual size.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>The size of the expertise die from flanking with your familiar increases by one step.</li>\n<li>You can cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.mac6yorikyk9li9d]{Chains of Hell} once per long rest without a spell slot. If you can cast 3rd level spells or gain the ability to cast them as either a wielder or warlock after acquiring this feat, you also learn it as your choice of a warlock or wielder spell. It does not count against your spells known.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
